1
00:00:55,789 --> 00:00:58,859
Man:
 Hello there. I'm your guide 
 and you're playing

2
00:00:58,892 --> 00:01:01,162
"You Don't Know Jack."

3
00:01:01,195 --> 00:01:04,098
And I need to know how many 
 contestants we have.

4
00:01:04,132 --> 00:01:05,866
Okay, sleepy, 
 let's try that again.

5
00:01:05,899 --> 00:01:09,103
How many people 
 are playing the game?

6
00:01:09,137 --> 00:01:11,672
I'm sorry, was I talking 
 too quiet for you?

7
00:01:11,705 --> 00:01:13,841
( shouts )
 How many people 
 are playing the game?

8
00:01:17,178 --> 00:01:21,349
So, you're all alone 
 playing with yourself, huh?

9
00:01:21,382 --> 00:01:23,184
God, I hate
this stupid game.

10
00:01:28,156 --> 00:01:29,790
( sighs )

11
00:01:52,946 --> 00:01:55,716
- Morning, Garnet!
- Morning yourself.

12
00:01:57,618 --> 00:01:59,253
She's been up
all night again.

13
00:01:59,287 --> 00:02:01,889
Mike Senior's
gonna wanna know.

14
00:02:01,922 --> 00:02:04,792
Woman:
 Why don't you call him 
 at the ranch?

15
00:02:10,331 --> 00:02:12,833
-( low growling )
- Man: Keith.

16
00:02:12,866 --> 00:02:16,170
Aw, come on, Mike.
Garnet's busy doctoring.

17
00:02:16,204 --> 00:02:17,938
She asked me
to feed the bull
just this once.

18
00:02:17,971 --> 00:02:20,708
Keith,
uh-uh.

19
00:02:20,741 --> 00:02:22,643
( sighs )

20
00:02:22,676 --> 00:02:24,312
Why you wanna make her
come all the way out here

21
00:02:24,345 --> 00:02:26,180
to feed that bull
is beyond me.

22
00:02:26,214 --> 00:02:28,349
I want her to come out here
so I can keep an eye on her.

23
00:02:28,382 --> 00:02:31,319
- See how she's doing.
- ( bull moos )

24
00:02:31,352 --> 00:02:34,388
I figured,
well, if she starts
working 80 hours a week,

25
00:02:34,422 --> 00:02:36,324
she'd work Mike
off her mind.

26
00:02:36,357 --> 00:02:37,825
- Mike: That's what I wanted. 
- Keith: Oh, jeez.

27
00:02:37,858 --> 00:02:40,328
Oop! Ah!
Get away! Ow!

28
00:02:40,361 --> 00:02:41,762
Oop!

29
00:02:41,795 --> 00:02:43,264
- ( Mike chuckles )
- ( Keith mutters )

30
00:02:43,297 --> 00:02:45,199
( horse whinnies )

31
00:02:45,233 --> 00:02:48,869
Mike: How long's
it been since you
saw Garnet laugh?

32
00:02:48,902 --> 00:02:50,037
I don't know.

33
00:02:50,070 --> 00:02:53,907
I figured
she bought that bull
and she'd shoot it.

34
00:02:53,941 --> 00:02:56,344
That seemed 
 natural to me.

35
00:02:56,377 --> 00:02:59,213
Well, buyin' that bull
that busted his head don't
seem natural to me.

36
00:02:59,247 --> 00:03:01,282
Well, that's because
you're an ignorant savage,
you see?

37
00:03:01,315 --> 00:03:03,217
That's psychology.

38
00:03:03,251 --> 00:03:05,753
Keith:
 You call keeping the bull that 
 killed your son psychology?

39
00:03:05,786 --> 00:03:08,856
Now here's what
I want you to do.

40
00:03:08,889 --> 00:03:11,359
I want you to get
on the telephone,
call Garnet up.

41
00:03:11,392 --> 00:03:13,827
Tell her
to come out here
and feed her own bull.

42
00:03:13,861 --> 00:03:15,463
That's not gonna
cut no ice with Garnet.

43
00:03:15,496 --> 00:03:17,498
You're gonna have
to be happy bossing
everybody else

44
00:03:17,531 --> 00:03:20,368
- in the county around.
- Now, she's my family
and I love her

45
00:03:20,401 --> 00:03:22,370
and I don't
want to see her
to suffer anymore.

46
00:03:22,403 --> 00:03:24,438
Well, if you wouldn't
make her haul out here
every night

47
00:03:24,472 --> 00:03:26,907
to feed that hay burner,
maybe she'd have time to find
herself another man.

48
00:03:26,940 --> 00:03:28,909
She don't want
another man.

49
00:03:28,942 --> 00:03:31,379
She just growls at 'em
and they run off.

50
00:03:31,412 --> 00:03:33,381
I've gotta find some way
to make one of them

51
00:03:33,414 --> 00:03:35,383
stand and fight,
but how do I do that?

52
00:03:35,416 --> 00:03:37,285
Well, why don't you
give them some horses
or something,

53
00:03:37,318 --> 00:03:39,253
'cause that's what
I think "ignorant
savages" would do.

54
00:03:39,287 --> 00:03:40,854
Horses.

55
00:03:40,888 --> 00:03:43,824
That's the dumbest idea
I ever heard in my life.

56
00:03:49,963 --> 00:03:52,300
They told me you were
back in town, Marshal.

57
00:03:52,333 --> 00:03:54,402
I swore 
 I wouldn't come.

58
00:03:54,435 --> 00:03:57,871
I heard that there
were knife wounds.

59
00:03:59,340 --> 00:04:03,844
- Here and here.
- They got better.

60
00:04:03,877 --> 00:04:06,547
Only because the ancient
Blackfoot medicine man

61
00:04:06,580 --> 00:04:11,285
pressed his magic talisman
to the wounds.

62
00:04:11,319 --> 00:04:14,722
- Hmm. Breathe.
- ( boy pants )

63
00:04:14,755 --> 00:04:17,891
"Hunda-hunda,"
breathe.

64
00:04:17,925 --> 00:04:20,928
I know I can't
hold you, Marshal.

65
00:04:20,961 --> 00:04:25,065
I know your job
comes first.

66
00:04:25,098 --> 00:04:29,470
- But can I ask
one thing from you?
- What's that?

67
00:04:29,503 --> 00:04:31,539
Would you pee
in this cup?

68
00:04:31,572 --> 00:04:35,476
- Hmm.
- ( chuckles )

69
00:04:35,509 --> 00:04:39,046
Hey, Ed, Sarah.

70
00:04:39,079 --> 00:04:41,014
Oh, I wear it
so a little boy
who comes all the way

71
00:04:41,048 --> 00:04:43,083
from Green River
will let me doctor him.

72
00:04:43,116 --> 00:04:46,354
- He prefers saloon girls
to doctors.
- Who doesn't?

73
00:04:46,387 --> 00:04:49,022
So, if you're a doctor
you can wear saloon dresses

74
00:04:49,056 --> 00:04:51,559
- or space suits
or whatever?
- Yeah.

75
00:04:51,592 --> 00:04:55,095
Of course, when you do,
good-for-nothings like
Jimmy Rawlinbow

76
00:04:55,128 --> 00:04:58,599
will stake out your office
looking for cheap thrills.

77
00:04:58,632 --> 00:05:00,868
Saw him on the way
in here.

78
00:05:00,901 --> 00:05:02,970
Yeah. I don't know
who's more dangerous--

79
00:05:03,003 --> 00:05:05,105
healthy guys who
play at being sick

80
00:05:05,138 --> 00:05:07,508
or sick guys who play
at being healthy.

81
00:05:07,541 --> 00:05:09,477
I took the stuff
and I got better.

82
00:05:09,510 --> 00:05:12,045
You're sick
and out of work

83
00:05:12,079 --> 00:05:15,483
and Wynette
is holding down
two jobs.

84
00:05:15,516 --> 00:05:16,917
I can give you
the medicine.

85
00:05:16,950 --> 00:05:18,419
Can't do that.

86
00:05:18,452 --> 00:05:20,388
They send me
samples, Eddie.
Free samples.

87
00:05:20,421 --> 00:05:21,922
They're rotting
in my cabinet.

88
00:05:21,955 --> 00:05:24,458
I pay my own way.

89
00:05:24,492 --> 00:05:26,394
If you wanna be macho
instead of healthy,

90
00:05:26,427 --> 00:05:27,528
I'm gonna come down
on you so hard.

91
00:05:27,561 --> 00:05:28,929
( chuckles )
Whoa!

92
00:05:28,962 --> 00:05:32,032
If you're gonna
kill yourself being a man,

93
00:05:32,065 --> 00:05:35,335
maybe you'd better
think about the people
that love you first.

94
00:05:37,971 --> 00:05:41,074
Sarah, darlin',
will you get Dr. Garnet
a drink there?

95
00:05:41,108 --> 00:05:42,543
Okay.

96
00:05:45,045 --> 00:05:49,517
It's okay.
You cry if you
need to.

97
00:05:49,550 --> 00:05:52,586
Crying's not going
to bring Michael back.

98
00:05:52,620 --> 00:05:53,921
( sighs )

99
00:05:53,954 --> 00:05:55,589
Could you take this
down to Arnel's,

100
00:05:55,623 --> 00:05:57,658
have the prescription filled,
and then drop it

101
00:05:57,691 --> 00:05:59,427
by Ed Pullman's place
on the way home?

102
00:05:59,460 --> 00:06:01,662
Why not call it in
and have them deliver?

103
00:06:01,695 --> 00:06:03,063
Because I need
to make it look

104
00:06:03,096 --> 00:06:04,865
like a free sample
from the office.

105
00:06:04,898 --> 00:06:06,634
I'd do it myself,
but I gotta go
to the ranch.

106
00:06:06,667 --> 00:06:08,536
Don't even start
about that crazy business.

107
00:06:08,569 --> 00:06:10,671
- Please.
- Okay.

108
00:06:10,704 --> 00:06:13,941
Jimmy Rawlinbow
is the only one left
in the waiting room.

109
00:06:13,974 --> 00:06:15,075
Do you want me
to send him in?

110
00:06:15,108 --> 00:06:17,545
Not really.

111
00:06:20,113 --> 00:06:22,416
Hello there, Jimmy.

112
00:06:22,450 --> 00:06:24,685
- You're gettin' to be
kind of a regular here.
- Yeah.

113
00:06:24,718 --> 00:06:26,954
Would you wear
that saloon girl
outfit for me?

114
00:06:26,987 --> 00:06:29,189
No, not even if you had
to crawl five miles

115
00:06:29,222 --> 00:06:31,559
on broken glass
to get here.

116
00:06:31,592 --> 00:06:33,694
I'd consider it.

117
00:06:33,727 --> 00:06:35,563
What's the problem?

118
00:06:35,596 --> 00:06:37,565
Well, I was helping
Tommy B. move yesterday.

119
00:06:37,598 --> 00:06:38,899
There was a lot
of heavy lifting.

120
00:06:38,932 --> 00:06:40,501
Oh, not
the hernia again.

121
00:06:40,534 --> 00:06:42,503
Jimmy, we've been
down this road before.

122
00:06:42,536 --> 00:06:43,637
I'm not impressed.

123
00:06:43,671 --> 00:06:45,539
( groans )

124
00:06:45,573 --> 00:06:47,941
All right,
let's get it
over with.

125
00:06:55,148 --> 00:06:57,485
- Still not impressed?
- Oh, stop it, Jimmy.

126
00:06:57,518 --> 00:06:59,987
I can't help it.
It's an involuntary
reaction.

127
00:07:00,020 --> 00:07:01,955
You're the doctor,
you take care of it.

128
00:07:01,989 --> 00:07:03,491
All righty, then.

129
00:07:06,594 --> 00:07:08,662
( snaps )

130
00:07:08,696 --> 00:07:10,464
- ( thumps )
- Oh!

131
00:07:10,498 --> 00:07:12,065
Good. 
 Now turn your head 
 and cough.

132
00:07:12,099 --> 00:07:14,602
- ( shudders )
- No, no, no. 
 Cough.

133
00:07:14,635 --> 00:07:16,904
- ( coughs weakly )
- Much better.

134
00:07:21,274 --> 00:07:22,943
- Hi.
- Hey.

135
00:07:29,983 --> 00:07:32,686
Now I'm gonna say
something to you

136
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:35,523
that you're not
gonna much like.

137
00:07:35,556 --> 00:07:38,492
But it's the truth.
It needs to be said
and I'm gonna say it.

138
00:07:38,526 --> 00:07:40,961
- Are you listenin'?
- Mm-hmm.

139
00:07:40,994 --> 00:07:45,065
You know how much
Michael meant to me.

140
00:07:45,098 --> 00:07:48,969
After my Ria passed away,
he was the only family I had

141
00:07:49,002 --> 00:07:50,170
till you came along.

142
00:07:51,605 --> 00:07:54,041
I love you, too, Pop.

143
00:07:54,074 --> 00:07:56,276
But watching you mope around
miserable every day

144
00:07:56,309 --> 00:07:58,679
is just too hard
to see.

145
00:08:00,814 --> 00:08:02,516
I got a hole in my heart.

146
00:08:02,550 --> 00:08:03,684
Well, then you
better fill it,

147
00:08:03,717 --> 00:08:06,053
because I can't
take this anymore.

148
00:08:06,086 --> 00:08:07,988
Oh, you can't?

149
00:08:08,021 --> 00:08:11,124
Well, I'm just as sorry
as hell for you, Pop.

150
00:08:11,158 --> 00:08:12,726
Now that's not what
I meant and you know it.

151
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:14,995
Sure, you did.

152
00:08:15,028 --> 00:08:17,030
You want to reduce
my personal grief

153
00:08:17,064 --> 00:08:19,066
to your not having
your own way.

154
00:08:19,099 --> 00:08:21,602
Well, if seeing me sad
depresses you,

155
00:08:21,635 --> 00:08:25,205
then you don't have
to see me anymore.

156
00:08:28,308 --> 00:08:31,579
Oh, hell.

157
00:08:37,685 --> 00:08:38,986
Hey, Cuddles.

158
00:08:39,019 --> 00:08:41,054
( snorts )

159
00:08:42,255 --> 00:08:44,124
Let's make friends.

160
00:08:55,268 --> 00:08:58,105
Come on,
you bastard.

161
00:08:58,138 --> 00:09:00,207
Let's play tag.

162
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:03,110
Hey!
What are you
doin' in there?

163
00:09:03,143 --> 00:09:05,679
( grunts )

164
00:09:10,751 --> 00:09:15,689
Look, having you gone
is a whole lot worse
than having you sad.

165
00:09:15,723 --> 00:09:17,725
Why don't you say
we cut a deal?

166
00:09:17,758 --> 00:09:20,193
What kind of deal?

167
00:09:20,227 --> 00:09:22,129
If you'll show up
at every event

168
00:09:22,162 --> 00:09:24,598
at next week's
Centennial

169
00:09:24,632 --> 00:09:27,067
with an eligible male,

170
00:09:27,100 --> 00:09:30,137
I'll feed your
dadgum bull for a year.

171
00:09:36,844 --> 00:09:39,279
( huffs )

172
00:09:39,312 --> 00:09:41,615
( phone rings )

173
00:09:45,786 --> 00:09:48,355
Aren't any of us
really sick.

174
00:09:48,388 --> 00:09:50,658
Mike called
a bunch of us.

175
00:09:50,691 --> 00:09:53,727
Rosie said you're looking
for dates for every day
of the Centennial?

176
00:09:53,761 --> 00:09:55,763
There's bound to be
lots of men asking.

177
00:09:55,796 --> 00:09:57,297
You're a pretty lady.

178
00:09:57,330 --> 00:09:59,199
- And what was
Mike's offer?
- Land.

179
00:09:59,232 --> 00:10:01,234
The Five Corners section
down at the river bottom.

180
00:10:01,268 --> 00:10:02,736
But that ain't it.

181
00:10:02,770 --> 00:10:05,806
You know I had a crush
on you since 6th grade?

182
00:10:09,276 --> 00:10:10,377
Ahem.

183
00:10:13,380 --> 00:10:15,315
She's got
a real nice
energy.

184
00:10:15,348 --> 00:10:16,784
Good grazin'
land, too.

185
00:10:16,817 --> 00:10:20,788
( sighs )
Can you believe it?

186
00:10:20,821 --> 00:10:23,691
He posted
a dowry on me.

187
00:10:23,724 --> 00:10:27,094
That old goat
put a bounty
on my pelt.

188
00:10:31,264 --> 00:10:36,203
( sighs )
So, he wants me
to get a man.

189
00:10:36,236 --> 00:10:38,806
Okay, fine.
I'll get a man.

190
00:10:40,207 --> 00:10:42,175
But I'm going
to own him.

191
00:10:43,811 --> 00:10:45,679
- I'll see ya, all right?
- Take it easy.

192
00:10:45,713 --> 00:10:47,681
See you next week.

193
00:10:50,851 --> 00:10:53,320
Woman:
 Bryan Jemsen, 
 I've got something here

194
00:10:53,353 --> 00:10:54,955
you're really 
 going to like.

195
00:10:54,988 --> 00:10:58,792
Oh! Sweaty!

196
00:11:01,829 --> 00:11:03,731
I gave the recording
of your symphony

197
00:11:03,764 --> 00:11:05,398
to a Hollywood agent
I know.

198
00:11:05,432 --> 00:11:07,935
He listened, he liked,

199
00:11:07,968 --> 00:11:11,371
he says he can get you
a lot of work doing
movies and TV.

200
00:11:11,404 --> 00:11:14,274
( laughs )

201
00:11:14,307 --> 00:11:16,376
- Movies and television?
- Yeah.

202
00:11:16,409 --> 00:11:19,212
- Well, that would be great!
- ( giggles )

203
00:11:20,948 --> 00:11:24,885
- How can I thank you?
- Come back to L.A. with me.

204
00:11:28,889 --> 00:11:30,390
Jenny, you're one of
my most favorite people

205
00:11:30,423 --> 00:11:32,793
in the whole world,
you know that.

206
00:11:32,826 --> 00:11:34,227
But I'm not sure
if I can--

207
00:11:34,261 --> 00:11:36,496
If you really love me,
that's okay.

208
00:11:36,529 --> 00:11:38,732
This is
how you find out.

209
00:11:38,766 --> 00:11:41,468
After we've lived
together for a while,
you'll know.

210
00:11:46,039 --> 00:11:47,908
You won't be sponging
off me, Bryan.

211
00:11:47,941 --> 00:11:51,845
Besides, think of all
the fun we have together.

212
00:11:53,914 --> 00:11:56,950
You like it. 
 You know you do.

213
00:11:56,984 --> 00:11:59,452
( plays melody )

214
00:12:01,321 --> 00:12:04,391
You drove
250 miles for this?

215
00:12:04,424 --> 00:12:08,762
Jill, a professional escort
is exactly what I need.

216
00:12:08,796 --> 00:12:11,464
And I thought you didn't
approve of my line of work.

217
00:12:11,498 --> 00:12:14,201
Jill, I don't
want a romance.

218
00:12:14,234 --> 00:12:17,537
I just want
an employee.

219
00:12:17,570 --> 00:12:19,439
How about
George here?

220
00:12:19,472 --> 00:12:22,776
He's very, 
 um... talented.

221
00:12:22,810 --> 00:12:26,513
Um, do you have someone
with just a few wrinkles?

222
00:12:26,546 --> 00:12:29,783
Mario.
There.

223
00:12:29,817 --> 00:12:32,052
He's almost 28
and he's well packaged.

224
00:12:32,085 --> 00:12:36,023
- ( phone rings ) 
- Jill: Yeah.

225
00:12:36,056 --> 00:12:40,928
No, you're supposed
to be booked tomorrow night
at 7:00, not tonight.

226
00:12:40,961 --> 00:12:42,529
Sorry.

227
00:12:42,562 --> 00:12:44,832
You know, when I used to call
Michael at the ranch,

228
00:12:44,865 --> 00:12:47,901
he would always
have this way

229
00:12:47,935 --> 00:12:49,536
of knowing
that it was me.

230
00:12:49,569 --> 00:12:51,839
So when I'd call,

231
00:12:51,872 --> 00:12:55,909
he'd answer the phone
with, "Hi, hon',"

232
00:12:55,943 --> 00:12:57,978
without me
saying a word.

233
00:13:01,281 --> 00:13:05,953
And sometimes I would
catch him watching me

234
00:13:05,986 --> 00:13:09,990
when I'd be looking
at a...

235
00:13:10,023 --> 00:13:14,327
you know, a sunset
or a baby.

236
00:13:14,361 --> 00:13:17,965
I mean, something 
 profoundly beautiful.

237
00:13:17,998 --> 00:13:20,533
And he would
rather watch me.

238
00:13:27,140 --> 00:13:29,276
Do you know how
that makes you feel?

239
00:13:29,309 --> 00:13:31,845
( chuckles, sighs )

240
00:13:31,879 --> 00:13:34,314
I mean, how could you forget
something like that?

241
00:13:37,417 --> 00:13:39,386
I can't.

242
00:13:40,888 --> 00:13:42,890
And I won't.

243
00:13:47,527 --> 00:13:49,596
He sounds
pretty wonderful.

244
00:13:52,065 --> 00:13:55,568
Yeah. He was perfect.

245
00:13:58,906 --> 00:14:01,875
You know...

246
00:14:03,944 --> 00:14:06,479
I just may have
a guy for you.

247
00:14:07,981 --> 00:14:09,983
Tell me again why
I should do this.

248
00:14:10,017 --> 00:14:13,420
Because you love
your little sister?

249
00:14:13,453 --> 00:14:15,655
I'm hurtin'
financially here,
okay?

250
00:14:15,688 --> 00:14:18,926
- I really need
the commission.
- Use someone else.

251
00:14:18,959 --> 00:14:21,428
You're what she needs.
You fit the bill.

252
00:14:21,461 --> 00:14:23,931
- I told you.
I don't have anyone else.
- I don't know how to do this.

253
00:14:23,964 --> 00:14:25,432
I'm not gonna take
that lady's money.

254
00:14:25,465 --> 00:14:28,101
You don't have to.
I'll take her money.

255
00:14:28,135 --> 00:14:32,139
Bryan, Mom's therapy costs
and this could help.

256
00:14:32,172 --> 00:14:36,576
- Besides, it'd be
good for you.
- Good for me?

257
00:14:36,609 --> 00:14:38,411
What you need
is to stop, Bryan,

258
00:14:38,445 --> 00:14:40,981
and really think about
what you're doing.

259
00:14:41,014 --> 00:14:43,050
You write music
that will get heard someday

260
00:14:43,083 --> 00:14:45,919
with or without 
 Virginia.

261
00:14:45,953 --> 00:14:47,387
Jenny said
the same thing.

262
00:14:47,420 --> 00:14:49,589
Oh, she's good.

263
00:14:49,622 --> 00:14:53,026
Please?
It's the right thing to do.

264
00:14:53,060 --> 00:14:56,196
This is the doctor
who helped Mom.
I like her.

265
00:14:56,229 --> 00:14:58,198
I wanna help her.

266
00:14:58,231 --> 00:15:01,001
And how long
are we talking about?

267
00:15:01,034 --> 00:15:03,470
- Just a week.
- Five days?

268
00:15:03,503 --> 00:15:05,472
A week...
of sanctuary

269
00:15:05,505 --> 00:15:07,374
where you can take
a deep breath

270
00:15:07,407 --> 00:15:09,476
and think about
what you're doing.

271
00:15:09,509 --> 00:15:12,212
What if somebody
up there figures out
she's buying the service?

272
00:15:12,245 --> 00:15:15,082
- Look, there's no sex, okay?
- Damn right there's no sex.

273
00:15:15,115 --> 00:15:17,417
Worst that can happen,
you blow our scam.

274
00:15:17,450 --> 00:15:19,219
Of course, you don't
want her to find out
that you're my brother.

275
00:15:19,252 --> 00:15:20,954
That would really 
 be embarrassing.

276
00:15:20,988 --> 00:15:23,390
All she wants
is control of her life.

277
00:15:23,423 --> 00:15:26,226
Well, control isn't everything
that it's cracked up to be.

278
00:15:26,259 --> 00:15:29,162
Oh, it's okay for Virginia,
but not for the doctor?

279
00:15:29,196 --> 00:15:30,964
Come on.

280
00:15:30,998 --> 00:15:34,434
What she wants
is for you to help her
have some fun.

281
00:15:39,006 --> 00:15:42,175
If I do this,
you're gonna owe me.

282
00:15:42,209 --> 00:15:45,545
Maybe.
Maybe not.

283
00:16:16,643 --> 00:16:19,046
( sighs )

284
00:16:21,814 --> 00:16:24,117
Car troubles?

285
00:16:24,151 --> 00:16:27,254
Yeah, it's blockin'
my view.

286
00:16:27,287 --> 00:16:29,189
Older man:
 Pretty this time 
 of the year, ain't it?

287
00:16:31,591 --> 00:16:34,161
Hey, do you know where
Garnet Hadley's place is?

288
00:16:34,194 --> 00:16:36,463
Well, now, there,
then it's clear across

289
00:16:36,496 --> 00:16:39,266
the other side of town.
Now you could go down here--

290
00:16:39,299 --> 00:16:41,601
well, no, just go
down the street here
and turn left

291
00:16:41,634 --> 00:16:43,536
and go about two blocks
and then turn right

292
00:16:43,570 --> 00:16:46,239
and go about
three more blocks,
down Lincoln Avenue,

293
00:16:46,273 --> 00:16:48,041
and then when you get
to Franklin, turn left.

294
00:16:48,075 --> 00:16:50,143
Come up to a big,
large poplar tree

295
00:16:50,177 --> 00:16:52,279
and it's about
two blocks past that.

296
00:16:53,780 --> 00:16:56,083
Okay, thank you.

297
00:17:01,288 --> 00:17:04,091
I'll leave
my car here, okay?

298
00:17:04,124 --> 00:17:05,225
Sure.

299
00:17:08,128 --> 00:17:09,729
- Okay.
- Thanks, Garnet.

300
00:17:09,762 --> 00:17:11,531
He cut his hair with
the safety scissors

301
00:17:11,564 --> 00:17:13,066
and then while
I'm cleaning up
the hair,

302
00:17:13,100 --> 00:17:15,235
he eats the whole bottle
of orange baby aspirin.

303
00:17:15,268 --> 00:17:17,070
Yeah, well, he must
have been very depressed

304
00:17:17,104 --> 00:17:18,505
- about his haircut.
- ( chuckles )

305
00:17:18,538 --> 00:17:19,639
- Bye.
- Bye.

306
00:17:19,672 --> 00:17:21,708
Oh, gentlemen, howdy.

307
00:17:21,741 --> 00:17:24,077
Everyone, I have
an announcement to make.

308
00:17:24,111 --> 00:17:27,314
My boyfriend from Denver
will be arriving here
this afternoon.

309
00:17:27,347 --> 00:17:30,150
- Receptionist:
 He's here. 
- He's what?

310
00:17:30,183 --> 00:17:32,552
Jacob Barnes 
 told Barbie Spencer

311
00:17:32,585 --> 00:17:34,621
that a guy
with Colorado plates
was asking for you

312
00:17:34,654 --> 00:17:37,157
- over on Schilling.
- He's here.

313
00:17:37,190 --> 00:17:39,726
I gotta go find him.

314
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:49,236
Hey, Becky! Christine!

315
00:17:49,269 --> 00:17:52,772
Have you seen a new guy
wandering around here?

316
00:17:52,805 --> 00:17:54,741
- Girl: No.
- No?

317
00:18:05,652 --> 00:18:08,255
Where is this guy?
( sighs )

318
00:18:15,928 --> 00:18:19,232
( birds chirping )

319
00:18:37,684 --> 00:18:41,288
Excuse me? Excuse me?
Are you all right?

320
00:18:41,321 --> 00:18:43,323
I'm a doctor.

321
00:18:43,356 --> 00:18:45,592
Are you "the" doctor?

322
00:18:45,625 --> 00:18:48,261
Uh, yeah.
You must be the--

323
00:18:48,295 --> 00:18:49,929
uh-- wait a second.

324
00:18:49,962 --> 00:18:51,864
What are you doing here
lying on your back?

325
00:18:54,767 --> 00:18:56,403
I was arranging
some clouds.

326
00:18:56,436 --> 00:18:58,271
Pardon me?

327
00:18:58,305 --> 00:19:01,174
Well, my dad taught me.
He said if you lay flat
on the ground

328
00:19:01,208 --> 00:19:03,610
and use the Earth's power

329
00:19:03,643 --> 00:19:06,179
that you can push the clouds
around with your mind.

330
00:19:06,213 --> 00:19:09,216
( chuckles )
And does it work?

331
00:19:09,249 --> 00:19:10,883
Well, yeah,
if you're patient.

332
00:19:10,917 --> 00:19:14,387
It usually does.
But you tell me.

333
00:19:16,823 --> 00:19:19,859
Bryan:
 What do you think?

334
00:19:19,892 --> 00:19:22,329
How am I doing?

335
00:19:22,362 --> 00:19:26,633
Okay, okay.
Um... why didn't you
come to me directly?

336
00:19:26,666 --> 00:19:27,934
I-- I mean,
what have you
been doing

337
00:19:27,967 --> 00:19:30,370
wandering around
here for the last
three hours?

338
00:19:30,403 --> 00:19:31,871
How did you know
when I got to town?

339
00:19:31,904 --> 00:19:34,874
Well, you met Mr. Barnes
at about 10 after 1:00

340
00:19:34,907 --> 00:19:36,409
when you came
into town,

341
00:19:36,443 --> 00:19:39,679
who told Jan Hunt
you were looking
for me,

342
00:19:39,712 --> 00:19:41,248
who then told
Meg Spencer,

343
00:19:41,281 --> 00:19:43,883
who called
my receptionist.

344
00:19:43,916 --> 00:19:46,853
- That's amazing.
- Yeah, well, that's life
in Sweetwater. Come on.

345
00:19:46,886 --> 00:19:49,222
I mean, if you
let one word slip
around here,

346
00:19:49,256 --> 00:19:50,790
I mean,
this whole thing
could fall apart.

347
00:19:50,823 --> 00:19:52,325
What whole thing?

348
00:19:52,359 --> 00:19:54,694
Hasn't your boss
briefed you?

349
00:19:54,727 --> 00:19:56,929
Well, she said that we're
supposed to be lovers,

350
00:19:56,963 --> 00:20:00,933
but that we'd work out
the details here.

351
00:20:00,967 --> 00:20:03,436
I don't get this.
I mean, you're very pretty.

352
00:20:03,470 --> 00:20:05,238
Okay, stop.

353
00:20:05,272 --> 00:20:07,907
Save it for the public
when we've got someone
to sell.

354
00:20:07,940 --> 00:20:10,843
( engine starts )

355
00:20:14,814 --> 00:20:18,017
So what exactly
are we selling?

356
00:20:18,050 --> 00:20:20,887
We've been lovers
for the last six months.

357
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:24,457
We will inevitably marry
and live happily ever after.

358
00:20:24,491 --> 00:20:26,926
Bryan:
Okay.

359
00:20:31,898 --> 00:20:33,866
Why do we want them
to believe that?

360
00:20:33,900 --> 00:20:36,436
No, no, no, no.
There is no "we."

361
00:20:36,469 --> 00:20:39,439
Why I want them to believe,
that is my business.
Now, come on.

362
00:20:47,547 --> 00:20:49,482
- Kiss me.
- Hmm?

363
00:20:49,516 --> 00:20:51,518
- Oh.
- No, kiss me.

364
00:20:51,551 --> 00:20:53,986
Neighbors.
Don't look.
Kiss me.

365
00:20:59,459 --> 00:21:00,893
- ( splatters )
- Oh!

366
00:21:08,435 --> 00:21:11,471
- Not bad.
- Thanks.

367
00:21:13,406 --> 00:21:15,508
Now, take me
into the house

368
00:21:15,542 --> 00:21:17,810
and make it look
like you love me

369
00:21:17,844 --> 00:21:20,413
- and that you've
missed me.
- Okay.

370
00:21:25,918 --> 00:21:27,887
Oh--!

371
00:21:32,359 --> 00:21:34,361
Bryan:
Let me get
the door for you.

372
00:21:41,368 --> 00:21:44,837
Ahem.

373
00:21:44,871 --> 00:21:48,475
So, Jill told me
this odd little story.

374
00:21:48,508 --> 00:21:50,477
I thought maybe
you might help me
understand.

375
00:21:50,510 --> 00:21:52,912
Okay,
fair enough.

376
00:21:52,945 --> 00:21:54,881
Look, I'm a little
nervous here.

377
00:21:54,914 --> 00:21:56,883
This is all
very new to me.

378
00:21:56,916 --> 00:22:01,120
Yeah, yeah.
Why am I here?

379
00:22:01,153 --> 00:22:02,989
I mean, Mrs. Bray
down at the Food Mart

380
00:22:03,022 --> 00:22:04,591
says you're the prize
catch in town.

381
00:22:04,624 --> 00:22:06,959
You were talking
to Muriel Bray?

382
00:22:06,993 --> 00:22:08,495
If you were
asking about me,

383
00:22:08,528 --> 00:22:11,564
then she's gonna know
that we're not involved.

384
00:22:11,598 --> 00:22:15,001
I mean, Dan Rather
doesn't reach as many
people in Sweetwater

385
00:22:15,034 --> 00:22:17,370
- as Muriel Bray.
- Calm down. Calm down.

386
00:22:17,404 --> 00:22:19,005
I mean, we wowed
the neighbors.

387
00:22:19,038 --> 00:22:21,073
They think we're in love.
I mean, I know what to do,

388
00:22:21,107 --> 00:22:23,009
I just wondered why.

389
00:22:26,045 --> 00:22:30,116
Tomorrow my husband
will have been dead
two years.

390
00:22:31,518 --> 00:22:33,920
I can't forget him.

391
00:22:33,953 --> 00:22:37,023
Even if I am
"the prize catch
in town."

392
00:22:39,426 --> 00:22:42,629
Sorry,
that must be tough.

393
00:22:44,497 --> 00:22:46,899
Thank you.

394
00:22:46,933 --> 00:22:49,502
I think you mean that.

395
00:22:49,536 --> 00:22:53,573
Anyway, people around here
won't give me a break.

396
00:22:53,606 --> 00:22:56,509
I mean, they feel 
 that I have exceeded

397
00:22:56,543 --> 00:22:58,945
the socially acceptable
mourning period.

398
00:22:58,978 --> 00:23:01,481
Like there is
such a thing.

399
00:23:01,514 --> 00:23:05,418
Right.
Exactly right.

400
00:23:05,452 --> 00:23:08,455
Oh, gosh.
It's nice to
finally meet

401
00:23:08,488 --> 00:23:10,022
somebody
who understands.

402
00:23:10,056 --> 00:23:12,959
Well, I didn't say
I understood.

403
00:23:12,992 --> 00:23:15,194
I mean, isn't it possible
to love the man you lost

404
00:23:15,227 --> 00:23:16,996
and somebody else, too?

405
00:23:17,029 --> 00:23:19,866
Nobody could ever
replace Michael.

406
00:23:21,734 --> 00:23:24,471
Well, it's possible
that you can love

407
00:23:24,504 --> 00:23:26,539
more than one person
at a time.

408
00:23:26,573 --> 00:23:29,442
Really?

409
00:23:29,476 --> 00:23:31,177
Well, you don't
even know me.

410
00:23:31,210 --> 00:23:33,946
Well, I know
how you kiss.

411
00:23:33,980 --> 00:23:35,482
Yeah, well,
that was nothing.

412
00:23:35,515 --> 00:23:37,917
You should see how
I kiss people that I like.

413
00:23:37,950 --> 00:23:39,652
Tell me about it.

414
00:23:39,686 --> 00:23:42,622
I have to pretend to enjoy
kissing some very bossy,

415
00:23:42,655 --> 00:23:44,223
mean-tempered women.

416
00:23:44,256 --> 00:23:47,894
- ( knocking )
- Come here.
Come here!

417
00:23:47,927 --> 00:23:49,028
- Wha-wha-wha--?
- Come in!

418
00:23:51,631 --> 00:23:53,900
Oh!
Oh, Pop, hi.

419
00:23:55,768 --> 00:23:58,905
I just wanted to be sure
that you didn't think

420
00:23:58,938 --> 00:24:03,510
that I was being unfaithful
to Michael's memory.

421
00:24:03,543 --> 00:24:07,614
But when you
sent every bachelor
in the county

422
00:24:07,647 --> 00:24:10,650
to court me,
well, I knew
you were serious.

423
00:24:10,683 --> 00:24:13,920
And because I know 
 this relationship

424
00:24:13,953 --> 00:24:17,056
is really 
 the one for me,

425
00:24:17,089 --> 00:24:20,960
I felt it was okay now
for you to know about Bryan.

426
00:24:20,993 --> 00:24:22,228
- Hi.
- Hey.

427
00:24:22,261 --> 00:24:24,697
- You know...
- Yeah?

428
00:24:24,731 --> 00:24:26,733
this ain't
half bad.

429
00:24:26,766 --> 00:24:29,035
I never have been
an omelet man myself,

430
00:24:29,068 --> 00:24:31,003
but this is
all right.

431
00:24:31,037 --> 00:24:33,039
Reckon you can
rustle me up
another one?

432
00:24:33,072 --> 00:24:35,041
Uh... actually, no.

433
00:24:35,074 --> 00:24:37,744
I used the last
of the butter and
onions and bacon.

434
00:24:37,777 --> 00:24:40,179
I mean, I can try it
with grapes and popcorn,

435
00:24:40,212 --> 00:24:42,048
but I don't think
it'll be the same.

436
00:24:42,081 --> 00:24:44,517
That's funny.

437
00:24:44,551 --> 00:24:46,586
Well, you're more
surefooted in the kitchen

438
00:24:46,619 --> 00:24:48,054
than Garnet here.

439
00:24:48,087 --> 00:24:53,225
Well, yeah, sure,
'cause Bryan worked--

440
00:24:53,259 --> 00:24:55,562
you cooked
in a kitchen,
didn't you?

441
00:24:55,595 --> 00:24:59,566
Uh... well, kitchened
in the place for a while.

442
00:24:59,599 --> 00:25:01,634
Oh, is that a fact?
Place, huh?

443
00:25:01,668 --> 00:25:03,570
What place was that?

444
00:25:03,603 --> 00:25:07,206
A place called
The Brownstone
in Denver.

445
00:25:07,239 --> 00:25:08,608
Right, right.
Brownstone.

446
00:25:08,641 --> 00:25:10,577
Brownstone.

447
00:25:10,610 --> 00:25:12,211
Any reason
you wanna know?

448
00:25:12,244 --> 00:25:14,714
Oh, I might wanna
pay 'em a visit.

449
00:25:14,747 --> 00:25:16,282
And why is that?

450
00:25:16,315 --> 00:25:18,751
Garnet and I had
a little talk last week

451
00:25:18,785 --> 00:25:20,753
and a talk that would
have included you

452
00:25:20,787 --> 00:25:22,321
if you'd been for real.

453
00:25:22,354 --> 00:25:24,256
How long you two supposed
to have been together?

454
00:25:24,290 --> 00:25:27,727
Six months.

455
00:25:27,760 --> 00:25:31,030
You remember those
twice-a-month visits

456
00:25:31,063 --> 00:25:32,732
to the clinic
in Denver.

457
00:25:32,765 --> 00:25:36,636
Well, geriatrics
weren't the only ones

458
00:25:36,669 --> 00:25:38,705
I was seeing.

459
00:25:38,738 --> 00:25:41,140
If you've known him
longer than yesterday,

460
00:25:41,173 --> 00:25:43,843
I'll smile
and kiss a pig.

461
00:25:43,876 --> 00:25:46,245
Well, you just
pucker up, Pop.

462
00:25:46,278 --> 00:25:49,281
You're the one who
wanted me to get a guy,
remember?

463
00:25:49,315 --> 00:25:52,652
Well, I got a guy.

464
00:25:52,685 --> 00:25:55,354
- That is not your guy.
- Oh, yes, he is.

465
00:25:55,387 --> 00:25:56,723
Although,
by the looks
of him,

466
00:25:56,756 --> 00:25:59,726
I expect he'd warm
to the idea.

467
00:25:59,759 --> 00:26:01,728
Now I wanna know 
 what's goin' on here.

468
00:26:01,761 --> 00:26:03,596
I-- I-- look,

469
00:26:03,630 --> 00:26:06,365
I know this comes
as kind of a shock
to you, sir,

470
00:26:06,398 --> 00:26:08,701
but you're really
making more of this
than is necessary.

471
00:26:08,735 --> 00:26:10,737
Look, son, I'm trying
to talk to my girl.

472
00:26:10,770 --> 00:26:14,073
Do you wanna step
out of the way?

473
00:26:14,106 --> 00:26:15,775
No, I don't
believe I do.

474
00:26:18,310 --> 00:26:19,812
She's actually
got you convinced

475
00:26:19,846 --> 00:26:22,148
