01:17:10,159 --> 01:17:12,195
No, you stupid ox.

1224
01:17:12,228 --> 01:17:13,830
Pop, you're not
gonna help him.

1225
01:17:13,863 --> 01:17:15,631
Man:
 Hey, bull! 
 ( whistles )

1226
01:17:17,767 --> 01:17:20,336
Bryan, somebody just
told me that that animal

1227
01:17:20,369 --> 01:17:22,772
killed that woman's husband.
Now, you can't do this.

1228
01:17:22,806 --> 01:17:24,240
I'll be fine.
It's something
I have to do.

1229
01:17:24,273 --> 01:17:25,875
No, you don't.

1230
01:17:25,909 --> 01:17:27,811
Look, I have an
interest here, too.

1231
01:17:27,844 --> 01:17:29,312
Now, I know you think
it's noble or something,

1232
01:17:29,345 --> 01:17:31,347
but she doesn't
need this.

1233
01:17:31,380 --> 01:17:34,650
Right now she needs me
more than anybody
in the world.

1234
01:17:36,419 --> 01:17:39,355
I'm going
to the car now.

1235
01:17:39,388 --> 01:17:41,925
If our future
means anything at all
to you, Bryan,

1236
01:17:41,958 --> 01:17:44,828
you'll come with me.

1237
01:17:44,861 --> 01:17:48,197
Jenny...

1238
01:17:48,231 --> 01:17:50,700
I'm not in love
with you

1239
01:17:50,734 --> 01:17:52,769
the way
I should be.

1240
01:17:52,802 --> 01:17:55,939
It wouldn't be fair
not to love you
the best that I can.

1241
01:17:59,008 --> 01:18:01,277
I'm sorry.

1242
01:18:06,883 --> 01:18:09,252
Good luck, Bryan.

1243
01:18:14,257 --> 01:18:16,960
- ( bull bellows ) 
- Man: Make him come to you!

1244
01:18:18,928 --> 01:18:21,831
- Man: Open the slide! 
- Man #2: Watch his flank!

1245
01:18:21,865 --> 01:18:23,933
- Yes.
- You've gotta
stop him, Pop.

1246
01:18:23,967 --> 01:18:25,501
Man:
 Pull!

1247
01:18:25,534 --> 01:18:26,970
He can take a look.

1248
01:18:27,003 --> 01:18:28,471
Hey, bull.
Hey, bull.

1249
01:18:28,504 --> 01:18:30,206
- All right, shut that gate!
- Easy, easy now.

1250
01:18:30,239 --> 01:18:32,341
Keith:
Here, put this on.

1251
01:18:32,375 --> 01:18:34,778
- Is there anything
I have to know?
- Keith: Too late now.

1252
01:18:34,811 --> 01:18:36,813
Yeah,
there's a damn sight
you need to know,

1253
01:18:36,846 --> 01:18:40,216
but for right now,
just take a tight wrap

1254
01:18:40,249 --> 01:18:42,919
and keep 
 your weight back.

1255
01:18:42,952 --> 01:18:46,289
How do I get him to stop
if I wanna get off?

1256
01:18:46,322 --> 01:18:48,958
( men laughing )

1257
01:18:48,992 --> 01:18:50,827
Just keep your heels high
and your weight in the middle.

1258
01:18:50,860 --> 01:18:52,395
Here.
Put this on.

1259
01:18:52,428 --> 01:18:54,230
At least you look like
you know what you're doing.

1260
01:18:54,263 --> 01:18:56,332
( bellows )

1261
01:18:56,365 --> 01:18:58,467
I'm not gonna
watch this.

1262
01:18:58,501 --> 01:19:02,205
- Keith: Got your seat?
- I have no idea.

1263
01:19:02,238 --> 01:19:04,941
( grunts )

1264
01:19:04,974 --> 01:19:06,910
All right,
let him buck.

1265
01:19:06,943 --> 01:19:09,245
- Man: Come on!
- Bryan: Yah!

1266
01:19:09,278 --> 01:19:12,248
- ( crowd cheering )
- Ooh, oh! Whoa!

1267
01:19:12,281 --> 01:19:13,282
Oh!

1268
01:19:16,052 --> 01:19:18,988
- Hey, Garnet, you watching?
- Are you done yet?

1269
01:19:19,022 --> 01:19:22,959
I guess not.
Grab him again, boys.

1270
01:19:22,992 --> 01:19:24,460
- Whoa!
- Oh!

1271
01:19:24,493 --> 01:19:26,295
Woman:
 Go, Bryan!

1272
01:19:29,098 --> 01:19:31,367
- Whoa! Oh!
- ( crowd cheering )

1273
01:19:32,501 --> 01:19:34,437
Whoa!

1274
01:19:37,974 --> 01:19:41,044
- Will you please
stop this?
- No.

1275
01:19:41,077 --> 01:19:43,346
I'm begging you.
Don't do this to me.

1276
01:19:43,379 --> 01:19:45,448
Sorry.
I can't stop now.

1277
01:19:45,481 --> 01:19:47,884
Can't?
You mean you won't.

1278
01:19:47,917 --> 01:19:50,854
And you want me to believe
that you love me.

1279
01:19:50,887 --> 01:19:54,023
You selfish, pigheaded,
inconsiderate son of a bitch.

1280
01:19:54,057 --> 01:19:56,492
- I'm doing this for you.
- No, you're not.

1281
01:19:56,525 --> 01:19:58,261
If you cared
about me at all,

1282
01:19:58,294 --> 01:19:59,996
you wouldn't do something
that could kill you.

1283
01:20:00,029 --> 01:20:03,833
Just like Michael!
You think that he cared,
then he loved me?

1284
01:20:03,867 --> 01:20:06,002
Well, damn
the both of you!

1285
01:20:08,304 --> 01:20:11,007
( gate bangs )

1286
01:20:11,040 --> 01:20:12,441
Hey.

1287
01:20:15,044 --> 01:20:17,346
You okay?

1288
01:20:17,380 --> 01:20:18,481
I gotta finish
what I started.

1289
01:20:18,514 --> 01:20:20,416
I think maybe
you should quit.

1290
01:20:20,449 --> 01:20:22,418
( grunts )

1291
01:20:22,451 --> 01:20:23,552
Are you ready?

1292
01:20:26,422 --> 01:20:29,425
- ( bull bellows )
- ( crowd cheering )

1293
01:20:35,564 --> 01:20:36,866
Ah!

1294
01:20:36,900 --> 01:20:38,501
All right,
that's enough.

1295
01:20:38,534 --> 01:20:39,635
That's enough!

1296
01:20:39,668 --> 01:20:41,537
Are you hurt?

1297
01:20:41,570 --> 01:20:44,040
- Are you okay?
- ( moans )

1298
01:20:44,073 --> 01:20:45,875
Are you blind?

1299
01:20:45,909 --> 01:20:47,343
My arm feels like
it's been ripped off.

1300
01:20:47,376 --> 01:20:49,045
My testicles ache
and I'm bruised all over,

1301
01:20:49,078 --> 01:20:52,015
but you're missin'
the point-- I'm alive.

1302
01:20:52,048 --> 01:20:54,350
I can still die.

1303
01:20:54,383 --> 01:20:57,453
You still think by dying
Michael deserted you.

1304
01:20:57,486 --> 01:21:02,125
He didn't.

1305
01:21:02,158 --> 01:21:05,028
Love doesn't die.

1306
01:21:05,061 --> 01:21:07,330
Don't you get it?

1307
01:21:11,968 --> 01:21:13,937
You don't get it.

1308
01:21:47,436 --> 01:21:50,106
( car engines start )

1309
01:22:09,592 --> 01:22:12,661
Give you a ride home
if you want one.

1310
01:22:35,151 --> 01:22:36,485
( sighs )

1311
01:24:32,168 --> 01:24:34,603
Hey, Cuddles.
Hey!

1312
01:24:40,576 --> 01:24:42,311
Come on.

1313
01:24:44,313 --> 01:24:46,315
Go on now.
Leave me.

1314
01:24:46,349 --> 01:24:48,651
I don't need you
anymore.

1315
01:24:48,684 --> 01:24:50,686
Go on!

1316
01:24:50,719 --> 01:24:52,755
Good boy.

1317
01:24:56,292 --> 01:24:57,826
Wait.

1318
01:25:00,163 --> 01:25:03,199
Go get a horse
and take a rope.

1319
01:25:08,171 --> 01:25:10,873
You just released
about a ton of grief
in the neighborhood.

1320
01:25:10,906 --> 01:25:12,708
You wanna help us
get it back?

1321
01:25:12,741 --> 01:25:15,211
I don't want him anymore.

1322
01:25:27,323 --> 01:25:30,326
( piano music playing )

1323
01:26:03,359 --> 01:26:05,894
- Have a nice evening.
- Thanks.

1324
01:26:22,445 --> 01:26:24,713
- ( music ends ) 
- ( applause )

1325
01:26:24,747 --> 01:26:26,715
Thank you.

1326
01:26:34,490 --> 01:26:36,325
Is there something
you wanna hear?

1327
01:26:38,461 --> 01:26:40,396
Yes, there is.

1328
01:26:42,798 --> 01:26:44,700
You know, a guy
can get seriously injured

1329
01:26:44,733 --> 01:26:47,303
playing what
she wants me to play.

1330
01:26:47,336 --> 01:26:49,672
I'd still
go for it.

1331
01:26:50,973 --> 01:26:53,509
I'm not sure
I can manage again.

1332
01:26:53,542 --> 01:26:57,846
Exhausted me.
Left me drained.

1333
01:26:57,880 --> 01:27:01,517
Yeah, but you're
still alive.

1334
01:27:01,550 --> 01:27:03,686
I'm here.

1335
01:27:05,888 --> 01:27:09,292
So what's your request?

1336
01:27:20,303 --> 01:27:22,004
Can you play this?

1337
01:27:27,843 --> 01:27:29,978
Yeah, I know this one.

1338
01:27:34,883 --> 01:27:37,886
( plays slowly )

1339
01:27:48,897 --> 01:27:49,998
Please.

1340
01:27:51,900 --> 01:27:54,036
One more time.

1341
01:27:56,505 --> 01:27:58,841
Push the clouds around.

1342
01:28:10,486 --> 01:28:14,923
( playing softly )

1343
01:29:17,553 --> 01:29:20,423
( piano music playing )

